      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZANDA MAN (3) enjoys a big class drop from his last-start sixth in the Caduceus Classic at Listed level at Melton. Showed good ability when putting four wins together earlier in the campaign and a good draw can see him back in the winners' list. OUR ULTIMATE GRACY NZ (4) has led and showed plenty of fight to win her two starts at Charlton since a spell. Taking on a better line-up this time but both of those wins were from wider barriers than this so she can play a major role again. WILD BULL NZ (6) has been good from tricky draws in two starts since a Stawell win. Owns a strong strike rate at this distance and won the only time he raced here. TORQUE POWER (2) came from a wider barrier and produced a good effort last time out when third at Hamilton. Two-time winner at this distance and he is well served by this draw.",
